```sql
WITH item_sales AS (
  -- Get all sold items with their categories
  SELECT 
    oi.item_id,
    oi.order_id,
    p.product_id,
    COALESCE(c.name, 'Uncategorized') AS category_name,
    oi.quantity
  FROM order_items oi
  JOIN products p ON oi.product_id = p.product_id
  LEFT JOIN categories c ON p.category_id = c.category_id
),
approved_returns AS (
  -- Get one approved return per item (if multiple exist, pick the first by return_id)
  SELECT 
    r.item_id,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY r.item_id ORDER BY r.return_id) AS rn
  FROM returns r
  WHERE r.status = 'approved'
),
item_return_status AS (
  -- Mark items as returned or not
  SELECT 
    s.item_id,
    s.category_name,
    s.quantity,
    CASE WHEN ar.item_id IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS is_returned
  FROM item_sales s
  LEFT JOIN approved_returns ar ON s.item_id = ar.item_id AND ar.rn = 1
)
SELECT 
  category_name,
  SUM(quantity) AS total_items_sold,
  SUM(CASE WHEN is_returned = 1 THEN quantity ELSE 0 END) AS total_items_returned,
  ROUND(
    SUM(CASE WHEN is_returned = 1 THEN quantity ELSE 0 END)::NUMERIC / SUM(quantity),
    4
  ) AS return_rate
FROM item_return_status
GROUP BY category_name
ORDER BY category_name;
```
